# Post-Claude Coding Review Checklist (Bring Back to Codex)

When you finish coding in Claude, paste these items here so Codex can do a fast, high-signal verification pass.

## 1) What changed
- PR/commit link (or patch)
- Files changed list
- Short summary of intended behavior changes

## 2) Which blockers were addressed
- C1/C2/C3/etc status (done / partial / not done)
- Any blocker intentionally deferred

## 3) Test evidence
- Commands run
- Results (pass/fail)
- Multiplayer repro steps used

## 4) Known risks after your changes
- Remaining race windows
- Remaining client-trust paths
- Any TODOs left in code

## 5) What you want Codex to check
- correctness
- exploit resistance
- architecture quality
- performance
- mobile UI

## Quick paste prompt for later
"I finished coding in Claude. Please do a strict re-audit of changed files, identify regressions, and give me:
1) must-fix before playtest,
2) safe-to-ship now,
3) exact follow-up patch list with file targets."
